{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-generic-show-tsx","path":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-discuss-your-morning-or-evening-routine/task-45","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"assignments":[],"bilibiliIds":null,"block":"learn-how-to-discuss-your-morning-or-evening-routine","challengeType":19,"description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Izraz <span class=\"highlighted-text\">feel groggy</span> je neformalni izraz koji znači osećati se slabo, umorno ili potpuno nesvestno/nebudljivo. Ovo se često dešava nakon lošeg spavanja ili kada neko naglo ustane. Na primer:</p>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">I feel groggy if I don't get enough sleep.</span> - Ovde, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">groggy</span> objašnjava umor usled lošeg spavanja.</p>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Sluggish</span> To je pridev koji znači spor, sa malo energije ili malim očima. Može opisati ljude, životinje ili čak mašine. Na primer:</p>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">I felt sluggish after lunch, so it was hard to focus on work.</span> - Ovo znači da se osećate sporo i umorno, a ne previše snažno.</p>\n</section>","nodules":null,"explanation":null,"helpCategory":"English","instructions":"","fields":{"slug":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-discuss-your-morning-or-evening-routine/task-45"},"questions":[{"text":"<p>Šta znači stručnjak kada kaže <span class=\"highlighted-text\">you may feel groggy during the day</span>?</p>","answers":[{"answer":"<p>Imaćeš mnogo energije tokom dana.</p>","feedback":"<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Feeling groggy</span> pokazuje smanjenje snage, a ne povećanje snage.</p>","audioId":null},{"answer":"<p>Nećeš moći da spavaš tokom dana.</p>","feedback":"<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Feeling groggy</span> Često je povezano sa potrebom za više odmora, a ne sa njegovim nedostatkom.</p>","audioId":null},{"answer":"<p>Možeš da osetiš umorne ili pospanosti tokom dana.</p>","feedback":null,"audioId":null},{"answer":"<p>Ćeš se veoma mnogo osećati.</p>","feedback":"<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Feeling groggy</span> ukazuje na umor očiju ili osećaj pospanosti, a ne stanje prevelike budnosti.</p>","audioId":null}],"solution":3}],"scene":{"setup":{"background":"interview-room1.png","characters":[{"character":"Expert","position":{"x":50,"y":15,"z":1.2},"opacity":0}],"audio":{"filename":"2.2-2.mp3","startTime":1,"startTimestamp":8.98,"finishTimestamp":19.58},"alwaysShowDialogue":null},"commands":[{"background":null,"character":"Expert","position":null,"opacity":1,"startTime":0,"finishTime":null,"dialogue":null},{"background":null,"character":"Expert","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":1,"finishTime":6.42,"dialogue":{"text":"Absolutely. My first suggestion is to not hit the snooze button multiple times.","align":"center"}},{"background":null,"character":"Expert","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":7.08,"finishTime":11.6,"dialogue":{"text":"It may be tempting, but it disrupts your sleep cycle and you may feel groggy during the day.","align":"center"}},{"background":null,"character":"Expert","position":null,"opacity":0,"startTime":12.1,"finishTime":null,"dialogue":null}]},"superBlock":"a2-english-for-developers","tests":[],"title":"Vežba 45","transcript":null,"translationPending":false,"videoId":null,"videoLocaleIds":null}}},"pageContext":{"challengeMeta":{"blockHashSlug":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/#learn-how-to-discuss-your-morning-or-evening-routine","dashedName":"task-45","certification":"a2-english-for-developers","disableLoopProtectTests":false,"disableLoopProtectPreview":false,"superBlock":"a2-english-for-developers","chapter":null,"module":null,"block":"learn-how-to-discuss-your-morning-or-evening-routine","isFirstStep":false,"template":null,"required":[],"isLastChallengeInBlock":false,"nextChallengePath":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-discuss-your-morning-or-evening-routine/task-46","prevChallengePat